        introduction: "Valence is often called the Gateway to the South as it marks the transition between the continental climate of the north and the Mediterranean climate of the south. This unique geographical position is reflected in the architecture, vegetation and gastronomy. The city is also an important university and economic hub, with many companies in the agri-food and logistics sectors. The taxi from Lyon is ideal for business travellers with meetings in the Valence-Romans business zone or for gourmets visiting the famous Maison Pic. Wine lovers particularly enjoy this route through the prestigious Côte-Rôtie, Condrieu and Hermitage appellations. TaxiNeo offers a comfortable transfer with a guaranteed fixed rate, allowing you to enjoy the scenery without the stress of driving on this very busy route.",
