        introduction: "Villefranche-sur-Saône, nicknamed 'Villefranche' or 'Calade' by its residents, is far more than a simple stopover town on the northern route. As the historic capital of Beaujolais, it is the beating heart of a world-famous wine region that each year produces the celebrated Beaujolais Nouveau, whose release on the third Thursday of November is a global event. The town has a strong identity, with its nearly two-kilometre-long Rue Nationale, lined with Renaissance houses featuring remarkable inner courtyards classified as historic monuments. Villefranche is also an important economic hub in the Rhône department, with companies in the mechanical engineering, textile and logistics sectors. The taxi from Lyon is ideal for professionals heading to the Villefranche-Limas or Arnas industrial zones, as well as wine enthusiasts wanting to explore Beaujolais cellars without worrying about driving. TaxiNeo offers a guaranteed fixed rate for this short journey, providing comfort and punctuality that public transport cannot match.",
