        itineraire: "The journey begins in Lyon, from any address in the metropolis. The driver takes the Fourvière tunnel or the southern ring road to reach the A7, the legendary Autoroute du Soleil linking Paris to Marseille. You first pass the industrial quaysides of southern Lyon, then cross the commune of Pierre-Bénite and the confluence of the Gier with the Rhône at Givors. The landscape quickly becomes greener with the Pilat hills on the left and vine-covered slopes on the right. After the Vienne toll (approximately €2.80, included in the fare), you can see the town below with its old rooftops, bell towers and the powerful Rhône flowing through it. The Vienne-Nord exit leads directly to the ancient theatre and historic centre, while the Vienne-Sud exit serves the residential areas and the Saint-Romain-en-Gal museum. Under normal conditions, the journey is smooth and pleasant, a true delight with the Rhône Valley panorama.",
